The more fancied Argentina capitalised on some Tongan handling errors in the first half to race to a quick lead and resisted a brave fight-back from the underdogs in an entertaining match at the Hanazono Rugby Stadium. HIGASHIOSAKAA - A first-half hat-trick by hooker Julian Montoya was enough to give Argentina a bonus-point win against Tonga at the Rugby World Cup, beating the spirited Pacific islanders 28-12 on Saturday. The more fancied Argentina capitalised on some Tongan handling errors in the first half to race to a quick lead and resisted a brave fight-back from the underdogs in an entertaining match at the Hanazono Rugby Stadium.